Theme: Moral "truth" through naturalism
Time Period: Early Renaissance
Artwork: Masaccio, The Tribute Money
Medium: Fresco painting
Prompt: Create a wall painting using natural colors on wet plaster. Show a group of people standing in a realistic outdoor space with mountains and buildings behind them. Use linear perspective so the background looks like it goes back into the distance. The people should have real‑looking bodies, natural facial expressions, and soft shadows that make them look 3D. The light should come from one direction, and the scene should feel calm and balanced.
Purpose: This artwork shows the new ideas of the Early Renaissance, when artists focused on realism, human emotion, and science. People were starting to study math and perspective to make paintings look more believable. Artists also cared about showing real human experiences, which is part of humanism. This kind of artwork was meant to help people understand religious stories by making them look like they were happening in the real world.
